{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"97b52de6-dfe3-4bf5-bd93-ac7bdab19d48","content":"Here are the issues I found:\n\n1. **`targetFramework` default not in choices** (line 10) — `defaultValue` is `\"net7.0\"` but the only choices are `net8.0` and `net9.0`.\n\n2. **`maxRetries` default is not an integer** (line 24) — `datatype` is `\"int\"` but `defaultValue` is `\"abc\"`.\n\n3. **`computed1` missing `value`** (line 26–28) — Computed symbols require a `value` expression.\n\n4. **`generated1` missing `generator`** (line 29–31) — Generated symbols require a `generator` property.\n\n5. **`postActions` entry missing `actionId`** (line 34–36) — Each post action needs an `actionId` (GUID) to identify the action type.\n\n6. **Missing `identity`** — Templates should have a unique `identity` field.\n\n7. **`shortName` is `\"restore\"`** (line 5) — This conflicts with the built-in `dotnet restore` command.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"769ba668-261c-4a21-a85b-431826e7a480","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me analyze this template.json for issues:\n\n1. **Missing `identity`** — The `identity` field is required in .NET template.json files (or at least strongly recommended; it uniquely identifies the template).\n\n2. **`defaultValue` for `targetFramework` is `\"net7.0\"` but it's not in the `choices`** — The choices only include `net8.0` and `net9.0`, so the default value doesn't match any valid choice.\n\n3. **`defaultValue` for `maxRetries` is `\"abc\"` but `datatype` is `\"int\"`** — The default value should be a valid integer string like `\"3\"`, not `\"abc\"`.\n   \n4. **`enableLogging` has `defaultValue: \"yes\"`** — For bool parameters in the .NET template engine, the valid values are strictly `\"true\"` and `\"false\"`, so `\"yes\"` won't work here.\n\n5. **`computed1` lacks a `value` property** — Computed symbols need a value expression to function.\n\n6. **`generated1` is missing the `generator` property** — Generated symbols require this property to specify how they're generated.\n\n7. **`postActions` entry has no `actionId`** — Post actions need an actionId (a GUID) to identify which action to execute.\n\n8. **`shortName: \"restore\"` conflicts with the built-in `dotnet restore` command** — This could cause confusion or command conflicts.\n\n9. **Missing `sourceName`** — While not strictly required, it's a commonly expected field.\n\nNow let me compile the definitive list of issues I've found.","outputTokens":946},"id":"89abe0d6-aba8-455b-88c2-f17f645d6930","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:41:06.697Z","parentId":"7ac5561b-642b-4b05-975b-0d41358f15cd"}
